frame.name: Travel
frame.definition: <def-root>In this frame a <fen>Traveler</fen> goes on a journey, an activity, generally planned in advance, in which the <fen>Traveler</fen> moves from a <fen>Source</fen> location to a <fen>Goal</fen> along a <fen>Path</fen> or within an <fen>Area</fen>. The journey can be accompanied by <fen>Co_participant</fen>s and <fen>Baggage</fen>. The <fen>Duration</fen> or <fen>Distance</fen> of the journey, both generally long, may also be described as may be the <fen>Mode_of_transportation</fen>. Words in this frame emphasize the whole process of getting from one place to another, rather than profiling merely the beginning or the end of the journey. <ex><fex name="Traveler">Ellen</fex> <t>journeyed</t> <fex name="Goal">to Europe</fex> <fex name="Baggage">with five suitcases</fex>.</ex> <ex><fex name="Traveler">Samantha</fex> <t>journeyed</t> <fex name="Distance">2500 miles</fex> <fex name="Co_participant">with her family</fex> <fex name="Path">by sea</fex> <fex name="Goal">to China</fex>.</ex><ex><fex name="Traveler">The Osbournes</fex> <m>took</m> a <t>trip</t> <fex name="Source">from Beverly Hills</fex> <fex name="Goal">to London</fex> <fex name="Mode_of_transportation">on the Concorde</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Area
FE.definition: <def-root>This is the <fen>Area</fen> in which the traveling takes place. This frame element describes the enclosed area inside which travelling, of unspecified <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen> takes place. <ex>We <t>travelled</t> in Europe.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Co_participant
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Co_participant</fen> is the person or persons who accompany the <fen>Traveler</fen> on the journey.</def-root>

FE.name: Distance
FE.definition: <def-root>This FE dientifies the <fen>Distance</fen> traveled.</def-root>

FE.name: Duration
FE.definition: <def-root>This FE identifies the <fen>Duration</fen> of time during which the trip occurs.</def-root>

FE.name: Goal
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Goal</fen> is the location where the travelers end up. </def-root>

FE.name: Manner
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Manner</fen> in which the traveling takes place. <ex>The Brownie troop <t>travelled</t> <fex name="Manner">hurriedly</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Means
FE.definition: <def-root>The action done by the <fen>Traveler</fen> by which the traveling is accomplished. <ex>I <t>traveled</t> to London <fex name="Mns">by hitchhiking and walking</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Path
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Path</fen> is the route along which the travel takes place.</def-root>

FE.name: Traveler
FE.definition: <def-root>This is the living being which travels. Normally, the <fen>Traveler</fen> is expressed as an external argument.</def-root>

FE.name: Source
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Source</fen> is the starting point of the trip.</def-root>

FE.name: Speed
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Speed</fen> is the rate at which the travel takes place. <ex>The Simpsons <t>travelled</t> <fex name="Speed">at 60 km per hour</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Mode_of_transportation
FE.definition:
<def-root>The <fen>Mode_of_transportation</fen> expresses how the motion of the <fen>Traveler</fen> is effected, by their body or by a vehicle which holds and conveys the <fen>Traveler</fen>. Vehicles can move in any way and in any medium. They are usually expressed obliquely with 'in' or 'by'.
<ex>Barney used to <t>travel</t> <fex name="Mode_of_transportation">by bus </fex> a lot</ex> <ex>Strom <t>travelled</t> <fex name="Mode_of_transportation">on foot </fex> to see the Pope</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Time
FE.definition: <def-root>When the traveling occurs.</def-root>

FE.name: Reason
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Reason</fen> for which the travel is undertaken.</def-root>

FE.name: Baggage
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Baggage</fen> are the items necessary for travel that accompany the <fen>Traveler</fen>. <ex>Ellen <t>journeyed</t> to Europe <fex name="Baggage">with five suitcases</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Frequency
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Frequency</fen> with which the <fen>Traveler</fen> makes the journey.</def-root>

FE.name: Purpose
FE.definition: <def-root>This FE identifies the <fen>Purpose</fen> for which the <fen>Traveler</fen> travels, i.e. the future state of affairs that will hopefully come about.</def-root>

FE.name: Iterations
FE.definition: <def-root>The number of times the trip is traveled by the <fen>Traveler</fen>s.</def-root>

FE.name: Period_of_Iterations
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Time</fen> throughout which the traveling repeatedly takes place.</def-root>

FE.name: Travel_means
FE.definition: <def-root>This FE applies to expressions that indicate documents, money, tickets, etc. which allow people to engage in travel. <ex>He <t>traveled</t> to San Diego <fex name="Travel_means">on a standby ticket</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Depictive
FE.definition: <def-root>The state of the <fen>Traveler</fen> during the journey. <ex>We <t>traveled</t> around <fex name="Depictive">unencumbered</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Result
FE.definition: <def-root>The affect of travel on a <fen>Traveler</fen>. <ex>We <t>journeyed</t> <fex name="Res">to exhaustion</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Place
FE.definition: <def-root>The <fen>Place</fen> is the location of the motion. It describes the area in which motion (with a specified <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen>) takes place.</def-root>

FE.name: Direction
FE.definition:
<def-root>The direction in which the <fen>Traveler</fen> goes.
<ex>They began their <t>odyssey</t> <fex name="Direction">north</fex>.</ex></def-root>

FE.name: Descriptor
FE.definition: <def-root>A characterisitic of the traveling event. </def-root>

lexUnit.name: travel.v
lexUnit.definition: COD: make a journey or journey along (a road) or through (a region).

lexUnit.name: travel.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: journeys, especially abroad

lexUnit.name: voyage.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a long journey involving travel by sea or in space.

lexUnit.name: voyage.v
lexUnit.definition: COD: go on a voyage.

lexUnit.name: journey.v
lexUnit.definition: COD: travel

lexUnit.name: journey.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: an act of travelling from one place to another.

lexUnit.name: excursion.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a short journey or trip, especially one taken for leisure.

lexUnit.name: odyssey.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a long and eventful or adventurous journey

lexUnit.name: expedition.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a journey undertaken by a group of people with a particular purpose

lexUnit.name: commute.v
lexUnit.definition: COD: travel some distance between one's home and place of work on a regular basis.

lexUnit.name: peregrination.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: travel from place to place

lexUnit.name: pilgrimage.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a pilgrim's journey

lexUnit.name: tour.v
lexUnit.definition: FN: make a journey for pleasure to several locations

lexUnit.name: tour.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a journey for pleasure in which several different places are visited.

lexUnit.name: safari.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: an expedition to observe or hunt animals in their natural habitat, especially in East Africa.

lexUnit.name: trip.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: a journey or excursion, especially for pleasure.

lexUnit.name: junket.n
lexUnit.definition: COD: an extravagant trip, especially one by an official at public expense

lexUnit.name: traveler.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: A person who travels or makes a journey.

lexUnit.name: getaway.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: a pleasant vacation

lexUnit.name: jaunt.n
lexUnit.definition: FN: a trip, usually for pleasure and usually relatively short.
